com.moback.android

Class FileManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.moback.android.FileManager

  • public class FileManager
extends Object
    The FileManager exposes helper methods for initiating the upload and download of files. All file access goes on in serialized asynchronous tasks.

    • Method Detail

      • downloadFile

        public static NetworkDownloadTask downloadFile(String url,
                               String fileName,
                               android.content.Context context,
                               Progress progress,
                               DownloadCompletionBlock completion)
        This downloads a file with a given file ID and stores it in the app's local storage.
        (Note: The file is not stored in the cache directory, and must be managed manually.)
        Parameters:
        url - The URL of the file you want to download.
        fileName - The name you want to save the file as, inside the app's cache directory. Any pre-existing file will be overwritten.
        context - The context of the application.
        progress - The progress callback for monitoring the progress of the download.
        completion - The callback for when the download finishes.
        Returns:
        The download task, so that it can be canceled, if needed.

      • uploadFile

        public static void uploadFile(File file,
              Progress progress,
              UploadCompletionBlock completion,
              String description)
        This uploads a file and returns the MoBackFile in the completion block. The name of the file is simply the fileID as a string. (Note: The file is not stored in the cache directory, and must be managed manually.)
        Parameters:
        file - The file to be uploaded.
        progress - The progress callback for monitoring the progress of the download. Exception thrown if null.
        completion - The callback for when the download finishes. Exception thrown if null.
        description - The Description of the file to be uploaded.
